# Storage Package

## Purpose

`@dukkani/storage` provides file upload, image processing, and object-storage operations (S3-compatible).

## Core Modules

- `StorageService` (`src/service.ts`) for upload/delete/list workflows.
- `ImageProcessor` for image transformations.
- `env` and `client` modules for typed storage configuration and client creation.

## Dependencies and Boundaries

- Uses shared types and MIME helpers from `@dukkani/common`.
- Uses `@dukkani/logger` and `@dukkani/tracing` for observability.
- Must not depend on app-layer UI or route code.

## Operational Rules

- Validate MIME types and file size before upload.
- Generate deterministic, sanitized object keys.
- Keep environment-aware behavior explicit (`local`, `preview`, `production`).
- Prefer returning typed results aligned with shared storage schemas.

## Best Practices

- Keep upload logic in this package; apps should call package APIs rather than reimplementing storage handling.
- Use centralized env values from `@dukkani/storage/env` or `@dukkani/env`.
- Log structured metadata (not raw secrets or large payloads).
